userStories.notes:
File to edit: plugins/slack/src/tools/search-messages.ts (lines 90-98)

The current code accesses m.channel.id and m.channel.name directly. If Slack returns a match where channel is undefined (e.g., message from a deleted channel), this will throw TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'id').

Change the match mapping to:
```
matches: (messages.matches ?? []).map(m => ({
  channel: {
    id: m.channel?.id ?? '',
    name: m.channel?.name ?? '',
  },
  username: m.username ?? '',
  text: m.text ?? '',
  ts: m.ts ?? '',
  permalink: m.permalink ?? '',
})),
```

Also update the SearchMatch interface (lines 18-24) to make channel optional to match reality:
```
interface SearchMatch {
  channel?: { id: string; name: string };
  username: string;
  text: string;
  ts: string;
  permalink: string;
}
```

Follow the same defensive mapping pattern used in list-channels.ts (mapChannel) and list-files.ts (lines 74-83).
